{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866513236,"sessionID":"ses_2861f8d58ffeA2I83Wpw4C47Gn","part":{"id":"prt_d79e482c40011LW0rrr2X7M6Kl","messageID":"msg_d79e46d4e001rL5lOlMBzpP7Pe","sessionID":"ses_2861f8d58ffeA2I83Wpw4C47Gn","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义 (Session Store Interface Definition)\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define and implement a unified `Store` interface in `pkg/store` to persist sandbox metadata keyed by session ID, with support for Redis and Valkey backends. The Session Store provides the persistence foundation for AgentCube's session management, enabling:\n6: \n7: 1. **Session Persistence**: Store and retrieve sandbox metadata by session ID in JSON format\n8: 2. **Expiry Tracking**: Maintain a sorted set index (`session:expiry`) for garbage collection of expired sessions\n9: 3. **Activity Tracking**: Maintain a sorted set index (`session:last_activity`) for idle session detection and cleanup\n10: 4. **Multi-Backend Support**: Pluggable implementation supporting both Redis (go-redis/v9) and Valkey (valkey-go)\n11: \n12: This AR establishes the storage abstraction layer that enables the Router and WorkloadManager to manage session lifecycle, support session recovery, and implement idle/expiration cleanup policies.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Scope\n17: \n18: ### In scope\n19: \n20: | Item | Detail |\n21: |------|--------|\n22: | **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` |\n23: | **Core interface** | `Store` interface with 8 methods (Ping, GetSandboxBySessionID, StoreSandbox, UpdateSandbox, DeleteSandboxBySessionID, ListExpiredSandboxes, ListInactiveSandboxes, UpdateSessionLastActivity, Close) |\n24: | **Implementations** | Redis (`store_redis.go`) and Valkey (`store_valkey.go`) providers |\n25: | **Data types** | `types.SandboxInfo`, `types.SandboxEntryPoint` |\n26: | **Error handling** | `ErrNotFound` sentinel error |\n27: | **Singleton access** | `Storage()` function with `sync.Once` initialization |\n28: | **Index management** | ZSET-based expiry and last-activity indices |\n29: \n30: ### Out of scope\n31: \n32: - SQL database implementations (MySQL, PostgreSQL) - can be added later via same interface\n33: - Cluster-wide distributed locking (handled by Kubernetes controllers)\n34: - Encryption at rest (rely on Redis/Valkey TLS and Kubernetes network policies)\n35: - Multi-region replication (rely on Redis/Valkey native clustering)\n36: - Transactional multi-key atomic operations across different session IDs\n37: - Custom serialization formats (JSON only)\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: ## Design\n42: \n43: ### File layout\n44: \n45: | File | Role |\n46: |------|------|\n47: | `pkg/store/store.go` | **NEW** — `Store` interface definition, `ErrNotFound`, provider type constants |\n48: | `pkg/store/singleton.go` | **NEW** — `Storage()` singleton accessor, `initStore()` with `sync.Once` |\n49: | `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | **NEW** — Redis implementation using go-redis/v9 |\n50: | `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | **NEW** — Valkey implementation using valkey-go |\n51: \n52: ### Type definitions\n53: \n54: **`Store`** — Primary interface:\n55: \n56: ```go\n57: type Store interface {\n58:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n59:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n60:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n61:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n62:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n63:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n64:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n65:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n66:     Close() error\n67: }\n68: ```\n69: \n70: **`redisStore`** — Redis implementation struct:\n71: \n72: ```go\n73: type redisStore struct {\n74:     cli                  *redisv9.Client  // github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\n75:     sessionPrefix        string           // \"session:\"\n76:     expiryIndexKey       string           // \"session:expiry\"\n77:     lastActivityIndexKey string           // \"session:last_activity\"\n78: }\n79: ```\n80: \n81: **`valkeyStore`** — Valkey implementation struct:\n82: \n83: ```go\n84: type valkeyStore struct {\n85:     cli                  valkey.Client    // github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n86:     sessionPrefix        string           // \"session:\"\n87:     expiryIndexKey       string           // \"session:expiry\"\n88:     lastActivityIndexKey string           // \"session:last_activity\"\n89: }\n90: ```\n91: \n92: **`types.SandboxInfo`** — Stored document type:\n93: \n94: ```go\n95: type SandboxInfo struct {\n96:     Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n97:     SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n98:     SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n99:     Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n100:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n101:     SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n102:     CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n103:     ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n104:     Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n105: }\n106: \n107: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n108:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n109:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n110:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n111: }\n112: ```\n113: \n114: ### Operations Flow\n115: \n116: #### StoreSandbox (Atomic Write)\n117: \n118: ```\n119: StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)\n120:          │\n121:          ▼\n122:     Validate: sandbox != nil && !ExpiresAt.IsZero()\n123:          │\n124:          ▼\n125:     Serialize to JSON\n126:          │\n127:          ▼\n128:     Pipeline/Multi:\n129:     ├─ SETNX session:{id} <json>\n130:     ├─ ZADD session:expiry <expiresAt.Unix> {id}\n131:     └─ ZADD session:last_activity <now.Unix> {id}\n132:          │\n133:          ▼\n134:     Return error if any command fails\n135: ```\n136: \n137: #### GetSandboxBySessionID\n138: \n139: ```\n140: GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n141:          │\n142:          ▼\n143:     GET session:{sessionID}\n144:          │\n145:          ▼\n146:     If key not exists:\n147:          └── Return ErrNotFound\n148:     If exists:\n149:          └── Unmarshal JSON → *SandboxInfo\n150: ```\n151: \n152: #### UpdateSandbox\n153: \n154: ```\n155: UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)\n156:          │\n157:          ▼\n158:     Validate: sandbox != nil\n159:          │\n160:          ▼\n161:     Serialize to JSON\n162:          │\n163:          ▼\n164:     SET session:{id} <json> XX  (key must exist)\n165:          │\n166:          ▼\n167:     If SETXX returns false:\n168:          └── Return error (key not exists)\n169:     Note: Does NOT modify ZSET indices\n170: ```\n171: \n172: #### DeleteSandboxBySessionID (Atomic Cleanup)\n173: \n174: ```\n175: DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n176:          │\n177:          ▼\n178:     Pipeline/Multi:\n179:     ├─ DEL session:{id}\n180:     ├─ ZREM session:expiry {id}\n181:     └─ ZREM session:last_activity {id}\n182:          │\n183:          ▼\n184:     Return error if any command fails\n185: ```\n186: \n187: #### ListExpiredSandboxes\n188: \n189: ```\n190: ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)\n191:          │\n192:          ▼\n193:     If limit <= 0: return nil, nil\n194:          │\n195:          ▼\n196:     ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 {limit}\n197:          │\n198:          ▼\n199:     For each sessionID returned:\n200:          ├─ GET session:{id}\n201:          ├─ If key exists: unmarshal and collect\n202:          └─ If key missing: skip (orphan ZSET member)\n203:          │\n204:          ▼\n205:     Return []*SandboxInfo\n206: ```\n207: \n208: ### Constants\n209: \n210: | Name | Value | Description |\n211: |------|-------|-------------|\n212: | `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` | Key prefix for session data |\n213: | `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` | ZSET key for expiry tracking |\n214: | `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` | ZSET key for activity tracking |\n215: | `redisStoreType` | `\"redis\"` | Provider type constant |\n216: | `valkeyStoreType` | `\"valkey\"` | Provider type constant |\n217: \n218: ### Environment Variables\n219: \n220: **Redis:**\n221: \n222: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n223: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n224: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Provider selection (case-insensitive) |\n225: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | - | Redis server address |\n226: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Required unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n227: \n228: **Valkey:**\n229: \n230: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n231: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n232: | `STORE_TYPE` | Yes | - | Must be `valkey` |\n233: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated server addresses |\n234: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Required unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n235: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | - | Set `\"true\"` to enable `DisableCache` |\n236: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | - | Set `\"true\"` to enable `ForceSingleClient` |\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ## Impact Analysis\n241: \n242: ### Files created/modified\n243: \n244: | File | Lines (est.) | Type |\n245: |------|-------------|------|\n246: | `pkg/store/store.go` | ~80 | New |\n247: | `pkg/store/singleton.go` | ~60 | New |\n248: | `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | ~200 | New |\n249: | `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | ~220 | New |\n250: \n251: ### Downstream consumers\n252: \n253: | Consumer | Dependency |\n254: |----------|-----------|\n255: | Router (AR-009) | Uses `Storage()` to persist session metadata |\n256: | Session Manager (AR-010) | Uses store for session CRUD operations |\n257: | Idle Cleanup Controller | Uses `ListInactiveSandboxes` and `ListExpiredSandboxes` |\n258: | WorkloadManager | Uses store for sandbox metadata persistence |\n259: \n260: ### Breaking change risk\n261: \n262: - **None for existing APIs**: This is a new package\n263: - **Interface stability**: Store interface is designed to be backend-agnostic\n264: - **Key naming**: Uses namespaced keys (`session:` prefix) to avoid conflicts\n265: - **Error contract**: `ErrNotFound` sentinel provides stable error checking\n266: \n267: ---\n268: \n269: ## Alternatives Considered\n270: \n271: ### 1. Use Kubernetes CRDs for session storage\n272: \n273: **Approach**: Store session metadata as Kubernetes custom resources (AgentRuntime objects with session labels).\n274: \n275: **Rejected because**: CRDs have higher latency and are not designed for high-frequency read/write operations. Session storage requires frequent activity timestamp updates and fast lookups by session ID, which are better suited for in-memory databases like Redis/Valkey.\n276: \n277: ### 2. Use a single SQL database (PostgreSQL/MySQL)\n278: \n279: **Approach**: Implement Store interface using SQL with indexed columns for expiry and last_activity.\n280: \n281: **Rejected because**: While SQL provides ACID guarantees, it adds operational complexity (schema migrations, connection pooling). Redis/Valkey provide better performance for simple key-value operations and native sorted set support for time-based queries. SQL can be added later as another implementation.\n282: \n283: ### 3. Use etcd directly\n284: \n285: **Approach**: Store sessions in Kubernetes etcd with custom prefix.\n286: \n287: **Rejected because**: etcd is optimized for configuration data, not high-frequency session metadata. It would add load to the Kubernetes control plane and require careful quota management.\n288: \n289: ### 4. Use Redis Cluster vs. standalone\n290: \n291: **Approach**: Require Redis Cluster for production deployments.\n292: \n293: **Rejected because**: Both Redis standalone and Cluster modes are supported through the go-redis library. The implementation uses single-node commands (SET, GET, ZADD) which work in both modes. Cluster-specific configuration is handled via environment variables, not code changes.\n294: \n295: ### 5. Use hash tags for Redis Cluster\n296: \n297: **Approach**: Use `{session}` hash tags in keys to ensure all session keys map to the same slot.\n298: \n299: **Considered**: The current implementation uses simple prefixes. Hash tags can be added if cluster deployments require it, as the key generation is centralized in `sessionKey()` helper functions.\n300: \n301: ---\n302: \n303: ## Dependencies\n304: \n305: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n306: |------------|---------|---------|\n307: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | v9.x | Redis client |\n308: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | latest | Valkey client |\n309: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.x | Structured logging |\n310: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | - | SandboxInfo type definition |\n311: \n312: ---\n313: \n314: ## Verification\n315: \n316: ```bash\n317: # Unit tests for store package\n318: make test PKG=./pkg/store/...\n319: \n320: # Run with race detector\n321: go test -race ./pkg/store/...\n322: \n323: # Integration tests (requires Redis/Valkey)\n324: go test -v ./pkg/store/... -run \"TestRedis\" -redis-addr=localhost:6379\n325: go test -v ./pkg/store/... -run \"TestValkey\" -valkey-addr=localhost:6379\n326: \n327: # Build verification\n328: go build ./pkg/store/...\n329: \n330: # Verify interface compliance\n331: go build ./...\n332: ```\n333: \n334: ---\n335: \n336: ## References\n337: \n338: - [Session Store Design](session-store/design.md) — Detailed design document\n339: - [Session Store Specification](session-store/spec.md) — Functional requirements\n340: - [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client patterns\n341: - [Redis Commands](https://redis.io/commands/) — Redis command reference\n342: - [Valkey Go Client](https://github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go) — Valkey client documentation\n343: \n344: ---\n345: \n346: *AR-012 — Module: pkg/store — Language: Go — Size: S*\n\n(End of file - total 346 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义 (Session Store Interface Definition)\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine and implement a unified `Store` interface in `pkg/store` to persist sandbox metadata keyed by session ID, with support for Redis and Valkey backends. The Session Store provides the persistence foundation for AgentCube's session management, enabling:\n\n1. **Session Persistence**: Store and retrieve sandbox metadata by session ID in JSON format\n2. **Expiry Tracking**: Maintain a sorted set index (`session:expiry`) for garbage collection of expired sessions\n3. **Activity Tracking**: Maintain a sorted set index (`session:last_activity`) for idle session detection and cleanup\n4. **Multi-Backend Support**: Pluggable implementation supporting both Redis (go-redis/v9) and Valkey (valkey-go)\n\nThis AR establishes the storage abstraction layer that enables the Router and WorkloadManager to manage session lifecycle, support session recovery, and implement idle/expiration cleanup policies.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775866513219,"end":1775866513232}}}}
