{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866624122,"sessionID":"ses_2861f8d58ffeA2I83Wpw4C47Gn","part":{"id":"prt_d79e4a5d7001BUsfkMcgMgH247","messageID":"msg_d79e487900016CoBV2J8mR95sE","sessionID":"ses_2861f8d58ffeA2I83Wpw4C47Gn","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: Redis Storage Implementation\n\n## AR-013 — Redis 存储实现\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `pkg/store` |\n| **Language** | Go |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the Redis storage provider for the Session Store interface defined in AR-012. This proposal delivers a production-ready Redis backend that:\n\n1. **Implements the Store Interface**: Full implementation of all 8 Store methods using go-redis/v9\n2. **Provides Atomic Operations**: Pipeline-based multi-command transactions for data consistency\n3. **Maintains Secondary Indexes**: ZSET-based expiry and activity tracking for efficient garbage collection\n4. **Supports Configuration via Environment**: Flexible connection and authentication setup\n\nThis implementation enables AgentCube to use Redis as the session metadata backend, supporting high-frequency read/write operations and time-based queries for session lifecycle management.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Redis Implementation** | `store_redis.go` — Complete Store interface implementation |\n| **Connection Management** | Environment-based Redis client configuration |\n| **Atomic Operations** | Pipeline-based SETNX + ZADD, DEL + ZREM |\n| **Error Handling** | Redis-specific error translation to `ErrNotFound` |\n| **Index Management** | ZSET operations for expiry and last-activity tracking |\n| **Helper Functions** | Key generation, JSON serialization, batch loading |\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Valkey implementation (covered in separate AR or future extension)\n- SQL database implementations (can be added via same interface)\n- Redis Cluster-specific hash tag handling\n- Redis Sentinel or Redis Cluster automatic failover configuration\n- Connection pooling tuning beyond library defaults\n- TLS/SSL configuration (handled via Redis URL or library defaults)\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### File Structure\n\n| File | Role | Lines (est.) |\n|------|------|--------------|\n| `pkg/store/store.go` | Store interface and ErrNotFound definition | ~50 |\n| `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | Redis implementation with go-redis/v9 | ~250 |\n| `pkg/store/singleton.go` | Singleton accessor and provider selection | ~80 |\n\n### Redis Implementation (`redisStore`)\n\n```go\ntype redisStore struct {\n    cli                  *redisv9.Client  // github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\n    sessionPrefix        string           // \"session:\"\n    expiryIndexKey       string           // \"session:expiry\"\n    lastActivityIndexKey string           // \"session:last_activity\"\n}\n```\n\n### Key Patterns\n\n| Pattern | Value | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` | Prefix for session data keys |\n| `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` | ZSET for expiry tracking |\n| `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` | ZSET for activity tracking |\n| Session Key | `session:{sessionID}` | Primary key format |\n\n### Environment Configuration\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Provider selection (case-insensitive) |\n| `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | - | Redis server address (host:port) |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Required unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` (case-insensitive) |\n\n### Connection Options\n\n```go\n&redisv9.Options{\n    Addr:     redisAddr,     // From REDIS_ADDR\n    Password: redisPassword, // From REDIS_PASSWORD (if required)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Operations Specification\n\n### Ping — Connectivity Verification\n\n```\nPing(ctx)\n    │\n    ▼\nPING command\n    │\n    ▼\nExpect \"PONG\" response\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn nil if PONG, error otherwise\n```\n\n**Redis Command**: `PING`\n\n### GetSandboxBySessionID — Retrieve by ID\n\n```\nGetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n    │\n    ▼\nGET session:{sessionID}\n    │\n    ▼\nIf redis.Nil:\n    └── Return ErrNotFound\nIf other error:\n    └── Return wrapped error\nIf success:\n    └── Unmarshal JSON → *SandboxInfo\n```\n\n**Redis Command**: `GET {key}`\n**Error Translation**: `redis.Nil` → `ErrNotFound`\n\n### StoreSandbox — Atomic Create with Indexing\n\n```\nStoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)\n    │\n    ▼\nValidate: sandbox != nil\n    │\n    ▼\nValidate: !sandbox.ExpiresAt.IsZero()\n    │\n    ▼\nSerialize to JSON\n    │\n    ▼\nPipeline:\n├─ SETNX session:{id} <json>\n├─ ZADD session:expiry <expiresAt.Unix()> {id}\n└─ ZADD session:last_activity <now.Unix()> {id}\n    │\n    ▼\nExecute pipeline\n    │\n    ▼\nIf any error: return error\n```\n\n**Redis Commands**: `SETNX`, `ZADD` (expiry), `ZADD` (activity)\n**Atomicity**: All commands executed in single pipeline\n\n### UpdateSandbox — Update Existing Record\n\n```\nUpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)\n    │\n    ▼\nValidate: sandbox != nil\n    │\n    ▼\nSerialize to JSON\n    │\n    ▼\nSET session:{id} <json> XX\n    │\n    ▼\nIf SET returns false (key not exists):\n    └── Return error: \"key not exists\"\nIf success:\n    └── Return nil\n    \nNote: Does NOT modify ZSET indices\n```\n\n**Redis Command**: `SET {key} {value} XX`\n**Behavior**: XX flag requires key to exist; returns false if absent\n\n### DeleteSandboxBySessionID — Atomic Cleanup\n\n```\nDeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)\n    │\n    ▼\nPipeline:\n├─ DEL session:{id}\n├─ ZREM session:expiry {id}\n└─ ZREM session:last_activity {id}\n    │\n    ▼\nExecute pipeline\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn error if any command fails\n```\n\n**Redis Commands**: `DEL`, `ZREM` (expiry), `ZREM` (activity)\n**Atomicity**: All cleanup operations in single pipeline\n\n### ListExpiredSandboxes — Query by Expiry\n\n```\nListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)\n    │\n    ▼\nIf limit <= 0:\n    └── Return nil, nil\n    │\n    ▼\nZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 {limit}\n    │\n    ▼\nFor each sessionID in results:\n    ├─ GET session:{id}\n    ├─ If exists: unmarshal and add to results\n    └─ If nil (orphan): skip\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn []*SandboxInfo\n```\n\n**Redis Commands**: `ZRANGEBYSCORE` followed by pipelined `GET`\n**Tolerance**: Missing keys (orphan ZSET members) are skipped\n\n### ListInactiveSandboxes — Query by Activity\n\n```\nListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)\n    │\n    ▼\nIf limit <= 0:\n    └── Return nil, nil\n    │\n    ▼\nZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 {limit}\n    │\n    ▼\nFor each sessionID in results:\n    ├─ GET session:{id}\n    ├─ If exists: unmarshal and add to results\n    └─ If nil (orphan): skip\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn []*SandboxInfo\n```\n\n**Redis Commands**: `ZRANGEBYSCORE` (on activity index) + pipelined `GET`\n**Note**: Same pattern as ListExpiredSandboxes, different ZSET key\n\n### UpdateSessionLastActivity — Bump Activity Timestamp\n\n```\nUpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at)\n    │\n    ▼\nValidate: sessionID != \"\"\n    │\n    ▼\nIf at.IsZero():\n    └── at = time.Now()\n    │\n    ▼\nGET session:{sessionID} (check existence)\n    │\n    ▼\nIf key not exists:\n    └── Return ErrNotFound\n    │\n    ▼\nZADD session:last_activity {at.Unix()} {sessionID}\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn error if ZADD fails\n```\n\n**Redis Commands**: `GET` (existence check), `ZADD`\n**Semantics**: Returns ErrNotFound if session doesn't exist\n\n### Close — Graceful Shutdown\n\n```\nClose()\n    │\n    ▼\ncli.Close()\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn nil\n```\n\n**Redis Command**: `Close()` on go-redis client\n\n---\n\n## Helper Functions\n\n### Key Generation\n\n```go\nfunc (rs *redisStore) sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n    return rs.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n}\n```\n\n### Batch Loading\n\n```go\nfunc (rs *redisStore) loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx context.Context, ids []string) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n```\n\n- Builds keys from session IDs\n- Uses pipelined GET for efficiency\n- Skips nil results (orphan handling)\n- Unmarshals JSON for valid results\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n| Scenario | Redis Response | Return Value |\n|----------|---------------|--------------|\n| Key not found | `redis.Nil` | `ErrNotFound` |\n| Connection error | Connection error | Wrapped error |\n| Pipeline error | Command error | Command error |\n| SETXX miss | `false` / not \"OK\" | `errors.New(\"key not exists\")` |\n| Nil sandbox | N/A (pre-validation) | `errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\")` |\n| Zero ExpiresAt | N/A (pre-validation) | `errors.New(\"ExpiresAt is zero\")` |\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files Created\n\n| File | Lines (est.) | Description |\n|------|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | ~250 | Redis implementation |\n| `pkg/store/store.go` | ~50 | Interface definition |\n| `pkg/store/singleton.go` | ~80 | Singleton and provider selection |\n\n### Dependencies Added\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"encoding/json\"\n    \"errors\"\n    \"os\"\n    \"strings\"\n    \"sync\"\n    \"time\"\n    \n    redisv9 \"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n    \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n    \n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n)\n```\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Redis client library |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging for initialization errors |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| Session Manager | `Storage()` accessor for session CRUD |\n| Idle Cleanup Worker | `ListInactiveSandboxes` for GC |\n| Expiry Cleanup Worker | `ListExpiredSandboxes` for GC |\n\n### Performance Characteristics\n\n| Operation | Complexity | Notes |\n|-----------|------------|-------|\n| Get | O(1) | Single key lookup |\n| Store | O(1) per command | Pipeline of 3 commands |\n| Update | O(1) | Single SET with XX |\n| Delete | O(1) per command | Pipeline of 3 commands |\n| List (expired/inactive) | O(log n + m) | ZRANGEBYSCORE + m GETs |\n| Activity Update | O(log n) | ZADD on sorted set |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Use Redis Transactions (MULTI/EXEC) instead of Pipelines\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | True atomicity with isolation; rollback capability |\n| **Cons** | Higher overhead; blocking on server; overkill for independent commands |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — Pipelines provide sufficient atomicity for independent commands (no cross-key dependencies) with lower overhead |\n\n### Alternative 2: Use Lua Scripts for Complex Operations\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Server-side execution; guaranteed atomicity; reduces round trips |\n| **Cons** | Harder to debug; Lua expertise required; harder to maintain |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — Current operations are simple enough for pipelined commands; Lua adds unnecessary complexity |\n\n### Alternative 3: Use Redis Hash instead of JSON String\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Field-level access; partial updates possible |\n| **Cons** | More complex serialization; nested structures (EntryPoints) don't map well |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — JSON provides clean mapping to Go structs; full document replacement is acceptable for session metadata |\n\n### Alternative 4: Use Separate Keys for Index instead of ZSET\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Simpler mental model; key scanning for cleanup |\n| **Cons** | Inefficient range queries; key scanning is O(n) |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — ZSET provides O(log n + m) range queries essential for efficient GC |\n\n### Alternative 5: Cache Connection Options in Struct\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Reconnection possible; expose more options |\n| **Cons** | More complex struct; go-redis handles reconnection internally |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — Store client only; go-redis v9 has built-in connection pooling and reconnection |\n\n---\n\n## Risks and Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| Redis connection failure at startup | Low | High | `initStore` logs fatal via klog; operator must check configuration |\n| Orphan ZSET members after partial failures | Low | Low | List loaders skip missing keys; periodic full scan can clean up |\n| Memory pressure from large session sets | Medium | Medium | ZSET with Unix timestamps enables efficient expiry-based cleanup |\n| Pipeline partial failure | Low | Medium | All pipeline commands checked; errors returned to caller |\n| JSON serialization failure | Low | High | Input validation; proper struct tags on types.SandboxInfo |\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run all store tests\nmake test PKG=./pkg/store/...\n\n# Run with race detector\ngo test -race ./pkg/store/...\n\n# Run specific Redis tests\ngo test -v ./pkg/store/... -run \"TestRedis\"\n```\n\n### Integration Tests (requires Redis)\n\n```bash\n# Start Redis\ndocker run -d -p 6379:6379 redis:latest\n\n# Run integration tests\ngo test -v ./pkg/store/... -tags=integration -redis-addr=localhost:6379\n```\n\n### Manual Verification\n\n```bash\n# Build verification\ngo build ./pkg/store/...\n\n# Interface compliance check\ngo build ./...\n\n# Lint check\nmake lint PKG=./pkg/store/...\n```\n\n### Test Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----------|-----------------|\n| Store and retrieve sandbox | Success, data matches |\n| Get non-existent session | ErrNotFound returned |\n| Update existing session | Success, data updated |\n| Update non-existent session | Error \"key not exists\" |\n| Delete session | Not found on subsequent get |\n| List expired sessions | Returns only expired entries |\n| List with limit=0 | Returns nil, nil |\n| Update activity for missing session | ErrNotFound returned |\n| Orphan ZSET member | Skipped during list, no error |\n| Concurrent stores | All succeed (different session IDs) |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [Session Store Design](session-store/design.md) — Detailed design document\n- [Session Store Specification](session-store/spec.md) — Functional requirements\n- [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client patterns\n- [go-redis v9 Documentation](https://github.com/redis/go-redis) — Redis client reference\n- [Redis Commands](https://redis.io/commands/) — Redis command reference\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n1. ✅ All 8 Store interface methods implemented for Redis\n2. ✅ Pipeline-based atomic operations for Store and Delete\n3. ✅ `ErrNotFound` returned for missing keys\n4. ✅ ZSET indexes correctly maintained\n5. ✅ Environment-based configuration works\n6. ✅ All integration tests pass against Redis instance\n7. ✅ Race detector shows no issues\n8. ✅ `Storage()` singleton properly initializes via sync.Once\n\n---\n\n*AR-013 — Module: pkg/store — Language: Go — Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775866624022,"end":1775866624119}}}}
