{"type":"text","timestamp":1775866641761,"sessionID":"ses_2861f8d58ffeA2I83Wpw4C47Gn","part":{"id":"prt_d79e65e75001Fycn4YNbES437L","messageID":"msg_d79e638b3001647v3ktFztrSpk","sessionID":"ses_2861f8d58ffeA2I83Wpw4C47Gn","type":"text","text":"I've written the `proposal.md` file for **AR-013 — Redis Storage Implementation**. The proposal includes:\n\n## Summary\n\nThe proposal covers:\n\n1. **Purpose**: Implement Redis storage provider for the Session Store interface, providing atomic operations, secondary indexes, and environment-based configuration.\n\n2. **Scope**: \n   - In scope: Redis implementation with go-redis/v9, pipeline-based atomicity, ZSET indexing\n   - Out of scope: Valkey (separate implementation), SQL backends, Redis Cluster hash tags\n\n3. **Design**: \n   - File structure (`store_redis.go`, `store.go`, `singleton.go`)\n   - Key patterns (`session:`, `session:expiry`, `session:last_activity`)\n   - Environment variables (`REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED`)\n\n4. **Operations Specification**: Detailed flow diagrams for all 8 Store methods:\n   - `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`\n   - `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n   - `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`\n   - `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, `Close`\n\n5. **Impact Analysis**: ~380 lines of new code, dependencies on go-redis/v9 and klog/v2\n\n6. **Alternatives Considered**: \n   - Transactions (MULTI/EXEC) vs Pipelines → Pipelines chosen\n   - Lua scripts → Rejected (unnecessary complexity)\n   - Redis Hash vs JSON → JSON chosen\n   - Separate keys vs ZSET → ZSET chosen for efficient range queries\n\n7. **Risks & Verification**: Race testing, integration tests, orphan handling","time":{"start":1775866641759,"end":1775866641759}}}
